\begin_layout Subsection*
Longing and Scars
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At the edges of their shared Dream, Luminous see so many remnants of a lost
 things, of worlds that once were.
 The scars linger, older than humanity's earliest memories.
 We don't remember why, but the pain remains.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Through the generations, that dark legacy scarred us.
 Parents teach their children to be afraid, that dreaming too bright is
 dangerous.
 They want the best for them, and so ask them to blend in so they wouldn't
 be bullied for what they are.
 The cruelties of the world were always too large to fight.
 Survival was the name of the game from the beginning.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Luminous dream of better, because something stubborn in them cannot accept
 a world like that – and it was that spark that drove them to Blossom in
 the first place.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Flex Commentary
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
So much of Chronicles is about something lost.
 The Supernal Realms were cast aside from the Fallen World.
 Father Wolf was killed by his children, rending Spirit and Flesh asunder.
 The Beasts knew a time before the scale of humanity stretched the Primordial
 Dream thin.
 In a sense, it was Princess' main theme, and Luminous doesn't fully discard
 it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
It's a story about what humanity has built too, what we have done in the
 meanwhile.
 Hence, Luminous don't consider themselves heirs from a time before, unlike
 them.
 But they can't avoid the remnants – their Dream remembers, even if they
 don't.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
A Turning Point
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Humanity's story has been anything but static.
 The Luminous built their Dream in secret, as the world changed around them.
 There was a time before any Luminous knew how to veil their two forms in
 a Dual Identity, as there was a time before humanity could talk to anyone
 in the world with a few presses of a button.
 Perhaps for the first time in history, they see a way they can win.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The world stands on a precipice that cannot be backed away from.
 The same technologies and ideas that entrench the fears and greed of those
 in power empower those who hope.
 In today's world, the Hopeful can come together in a way they never had
 been able to before and Blossom in numbers not heard of since the heights
 of the Renaissance.
 Maybe, just maybe...
 something could change this time.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Flex Commentary
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
The World of Darkness is traditionally stories of survival.
 Luminous is not.
 Like the Sin-Eaters who wish to retake the Underworld, and the Changelings
 who wish to retake their life, Luminous wish to retake the waking world
 from the cruelties of those who don't care, the scars of generations of
 pain.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
It is no accident that, like those two games, its themes are brighter than
 most of the Chronicles of Darkness.
 Changeling is about recovery and moving forward despite once being hurt,
 Geist is about enjoying your second chance at life as you seek to do better,
 and Luminous is about those who seek to change the world as they lose themselve
s in their dreams.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

