\begin_layout Subsection*
Senki Zesshou Symphogear
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Symphogear follows the story of Hibiki, an ordinary girl who ends up bound
 to an ancient relic that allowed her to transform and fight the Noise that
 plagued the noise with the power of song.
 At its heart, it is a story about heartfelt communication that pierces
 misunderstandings, the determination to protect those you love, and the
 sacrifices one makes to do so.
 About the scars of the past, and what must be done to heal them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Even in the heart of darkness, Hibiki refuses to give up.
 She stays strong in her belief in the ability to reach to the heart, always
 fighting both physical battles and against people's own despair.
 Each member of the main cast suffers tragedy, and it's through their bonds
 with others that they're able to stand up again.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Magia Record: Puella Magi Madoka Magica Side Story
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The original anime, Puella Magi Madoka Magica, is already resonant with
 the themes of Luminous.
 For all it is praised for its dark themes, at its heart, Madoka Magica
 is a love story and a story of hope.
 Madoka Kaname shone through the shadows, to rewrite the world itself.
 More than any other character in popular media, she represents the kind
 of hope Luminous stand for.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Magia Record, then, pivots the focus more to the human responses to the
 woes of magic in a dark world.
 It, to some extant, embraces the story that always existed under the original's
 darkness.
 It focuses on relationships, girls pulling their friends from the brink
 of despair, and standing up for what's right.
 In the side-stories shown in the original phone game, it told the same
 kind of slice-of-life stories that Luminous embraces.
 Of magical girls caring for each other, of the bonds between them that
 let them survive in a dark world.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
The Lego Movie 2: The Second Part
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whereas the first movie focused on creativity and freedom, the second discusses
 true maturity.
 It shows that growing up doesn’t mean that the things you believed in when
 younger have to be forgotten and let go of.
 It tells of how even in a darker world, hoping is not in vain.
 The movie shows the world like Luminous see it; almost everyone else loses
 their flame, their light, their hope in the world, because they believe
 it’s the only way to survive.
 But it isn't true.
 The song Everything’s Not Awesome summarizes it all fairly well.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Chapter
Chapter 1: Shining Lights
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Luminous and their predecessors built the Dream they draw their magic
 from over the generations, hiding it away in the edges of their dreams,
 in a place where the dreams of humanity naturally bleed together.
 Their nature is as fluid and shifting as any other dream.
 Before Luminous were magical girls, they were the paladins in shining armor,
 the angels with wings of light, the witch in the forest, the village shaman.
 All dreaming of a better world, where they and those they love could simply
 live happily.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the moment they Blossom, they shape their soul into a world they call
 their Soulspace.
 They weave the symbols of the Dream together into a world reflecting their
 own deepest truths, and through that, they take on its power for their
 own.
 Three central symbols define who they are as a Luminous:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Their Luminary forms the foundation of their magic, reflecting their approach
 to the world.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The Kingdom they are a citizen of in their dreams, reflecting their vision
 of a better world.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Their Archetype shapes their Dream Form and how they project their will
 upon the world.
\end_layout

