So bright is the Sun, that its light defines the cycle of day and night
 itself.
 Those who follow the path of Sunlight vow to themselves do the same.
 They vow to be the ones to turn night to day, to shine for those who are
 lost in the dark.
 They are the beacons others look to, and the ones who light the path for
 others to follow.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They are the heroic warriors whose legends outlive them long after their
 time is over, the field scientists whose discoveries are cited decades
 later, the activist organizers who march among those they lead.
 The Sunlit, more than anything else, are the ones who shine brightly for
 all to see, the ones who act visibly in the open.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Magic:
\series default
 The magic of the Sunlit tends to be bright, colorful and personal, leaving
 neither what they intend to do nor their own nature particularly hard to
 read.
 Their transformations too are as colorful and distinctive as their magic,
 decorated with a crystal clear personal touch revealing their innermost
 truths.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The boy who was always bullied for how much he loved old stories of knighthood
 shines in defiance of the world every time he transforms.
 He carries on that dream regardless, wearing the same shining silver armor
 he always imagined when he read those stories, covered in both fantastical
 heraldry and futuristic lights and glows.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The elementary school teacher who always encouraged her students to be their
 best self teaches by example every time she transforms.
 She embraces her own childish nature, appearing as a young girl in a classical
 frilled magical girl costume long into adulthood.
 At the same time, she refuses to be defined as lesser for it, taking the
 lead as confidently, and expecting others to follow her regardless of her
 appearance.
 
\end_layout

