\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Transformation!Dual Identity|(textbf
\end_layout

\end_inset

The Hopeful derive one last benefit from their transformation: Their mundane
 and dream forms appear to be two different people.
 Regardless of how similar her two forms look, others around her treat them
 as if they had entirely different appearances.
 This is not exactly an illusion, as it does not change what people see.
 Rather, it simply prevents them from recognizing the two forms as the same
 based on such.
 This protection extends to magical senses such as a Vampire's taste for
 blood, or an Uratha's ability to track others by scent.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Supernatural powers used to try and link her two identities are similarly
 fooled.
 Powers that use Sympathy or Intimacy treat her two forms as separate –
 a friend who only knows her in her mundane form has no Sympathy with her
 Dream Form.
 Powers that determine information about a Luminous do not directly reveal
 information that connect her two identities, treating her (at best) as
 two people with close ties to the same friend group.
 That may still break her cover in the context of a full investigation,
 of course.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As powerful as it is, however, a Luminous cannot rely solely on Dual Identity
 to protect herself.
 It does not prevent others from suspecting a Luminous' nature based on
 circumstantial evidence.
 She cannot simply dip into a closet only to return as a mysterious magical
 girl, and not expect others to not draw the connection eventually.
 She obviously cannot transform in front of someone, and expect Dual Identity
 to protect her even slightly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In cases where she needs to intentionally prove her identity, she may spend
 a Willpower to drop this protection for the rest of a scene.
 This does not necessarily convince others that she is the same person if
 she looks radically different in her two forms, but it at least removes
