\begin_layout Section
Beast: the Primordial
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Interactions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Beasts see themselves as kin to all supernatural beings.
 Though the Luminous and Maou see themselves as humanity's own legacy, they
 are still supernatural enough for a Beat to make a connection.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Kinship
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Luminous in their Dream Form have the same Kinship with Beasts as Mages
 do, but they have no kinship in Mundane Form.
 With her mundane self grounding her in humanity, a Beast's arguments of
 Kinship often fall flat.
 Thicker Than Water has no effect on her in either of her forms.
 However, the Family Ties condition applies to both a Luminous' forms once
 established – assuming the Beast is aware of her mundane identity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Origins may chance a Luminous' Kinship, however.
 Luminous with the Spirit Origin have full Kinship in their Dream Form and
 none in their Mundane Form.
 Luminous with the Wyrd Origin have full Kinship, and Thicker Than Water
 applies to them.
\end_layout

